content.description: A variant of Cruiser traversing through the left topout.
content.location: Begin on the same center hold as Cruiser and traverse left up through the top left corner of the main boulder, same as Spice Run.

content.description: A shorter variant of Kessel Run starting on the same hold and traversing through good jugs.
content.location: Start on the far right lower ledge and traverse left to the middle topout on the main face.

content.description: A variant of Cruiser traversing slightly further to the right.
content.location: Begin on the same center hold as Cruiser and traverse further right up through the slightly tricky topout, same as  Pod Race

content.description: Same as Order 66, but with an earlier topout.
content.location: Start on the same holds under the landing in the pit area and follow the same problem as Order 66, but topout in the middle section of the main face.

content.description: Same as Order 66, but move straight up to a topout.
content.location: Start on the same holds under the landing in the pit area and follow the same problem as Order 66, but once on the ledge dyno up to a good hold and topout straight up same as Star Fighter.

content.description: The shortest variant of Kessel Run starting on the same holds but going straight up.
content.location: Start on the far right lower ledge and work your way up to a good pocket, followed by a slightly large move up to a good rail and top out up and right through a somewhat tricky finish.

content.description: The deepest section of the boulder in the dark depths of the cave.  Work out of a horizontal start and back up into the slopy arete followed by a long traverse into a topout.
content.location: Start in the middle pit under the landing rock with starting hands on the inside ledge and feet on the lower face in front of you.  Work your way to the outside ledge of the landing and move your way left into the sloping holds and eventually the ledge.  Traverse right and finish on the far right corner, same as Speeder.

content.description: Variant of Chosen One, but with a dyno move straight up.
content.location: Start down low in the pit, same as Chosen One and work your way up to the next ledge.  From there dyno up to a good hold and finish up to the left same as Star Fighter.

content.description: Variant of Chosen One, but slightly shorter with an earlier topout.
content.location: Start down low in the pit, same as Chosen One and work your way up into the traverse, but topping out in the middle topout region, same as Cruiser.

content.description: One of the longest problems on this boulder working from the right side to the left on the main portion of this wall, traversing through all nice holds.
content.location: Start on the large low ledge on the right side of the main face.  Traverse your way left up through the top left corner of the main boulder, above the pit landing next to the tree stump.

content.description: A short but smooth fun techy problem working through some nice crimps into a nice topout ledge.
content.location: Located on the left end of Galactic Variant there is a small overhung face.  Start on the good right rail and traverse left into two small nice crimps and move up to the top ledge them rock up and over the top.

content.description: A short problem keeping slight tension from a heel toe cam and walking your hands along the perimeter into the topout.
content.location: Start at the same section as Falcons Keel, but with your hands on the left perimeter of the face and a right heel toe cam.  Walk your hands along the perimeter to the top then rock up and over the topout.

content.description: A traversing problem working from the center of the boulder up through the topout.
content.location: Begin in the center of the boulder, on the left end of the main face.  Traverse right up through the middle face topout.

content.description: A fun tensiony problem on the underside of the landing boulder using a double toe hook technique and coding up to get around to a mantle topout.
content.location: Start under the right side of the landing boulder with right hand on a ledge on the underside and left on the left ledge right after the tree and a double toe hook.  Work your hands up and around to the top of the landing boulder to pull yourself up and over the top without dabbing.

content.description: A fun problem starting down low in the pit working through some slopers into a long traversing finish.
content.location: Start down low in the center pit on the large lowest (usually wet) ledge.  Work your way up using the small right face up to the large ledge to your left.  Traverse your way all the way to the right side of the face and topout on the right corner, same as Speeder.

content.description: This boulder consists of a decently long face with openings under the main landing. Includes several longer traversing problems.  There are about 5-7 unique problems with the rest being variants.  A fun boulder to mess around on with problems anywhere from V0-5.
